The paper focuses on self-supervised representation learning for images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of visual words and Bag-of-Words representations is also a common technique in computer vision, which further supports the classification of this paper under cs.CV. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning methods for representation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Bag-of-Words representations also has connections to natural language processing (cs.CL), and the paper mentions the potential for connections to related methods from the NLP domain. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on detection and classification tasks, which are common topics in information retrieval (cs.IR).
